The National Broadcasting Commission (NBC) has fined a media station in Jos for airing Nigerian songs which they claim contains “vulgar and indecent music lyrics”. The songs listed are Falz “This is Nigeria”, Olamide “See Mary, See Jesus” and Wande Coal’s “Iskaba”. The offensive lyrics are as follows: In the letter addressed to JODAJ Global Communications Ltd, they stated that the media station pay the fine of N100,000 according to section 14.1.4.1a. See the letter below: NBC Sanction